title: Almond Butter Zucchini Brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350Â°F. Grease a square (8x8) baking dish.
Grate the zucchini into a bowl. Add almond butter, egg, honey, and vanilla to the bowl. Mix well.
Add cinnamon, baking soda, and salt. Mix until all ingredients are evenly combined.
Bake for 20-25 minutes, until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
ingredients: 1 pinch sea salt, unrefined and pure
1/2 c. chocolate chips, dark, 70%, raw, organic
